# pyenv
#   For a library or app, you might want to share your .python-version if you're
#   using pyenv.
#   See https://github.com/pyenv/pyenv/blob/master/README.md#shared-version-file
#.python-version

# pipenv
#   According to pypa/pipenv#598, it is recommended to include Pipfile.lock in version control.
#   However, in case of collaboration, if delegates have different python versions passed,
#   Pipfile.lock might be overwritten, causing git conflicts.
#Pipfile.lock

# poetry
#   Similar to Pipfile.lock, poetry.lock can be gitignored or not.
#   https://python-poetry.org/docs/basic-usage/#commit-your-poetrylock-file-to-version-control
#poetry.lock

# pdm
#   Similar to Pipfile.lock, pdm.lock can be gitignored or not
#pdm.lock

